I am currently unable to create a pull request against any repository.

When I click the {{Create Pull Request}} button, it appears there&#x27;s an ajax call to {{/api/1.0/repositories/path/to/myrepo/pullrequests/tasks/<my pull request uuid>}} which gets the following 200 status response:

{{{"task":"<my pull requestuuid>","complete":false}}}

then it just sits and spins firing GET requests to the same url with the same HTTP 304 status response:

{{{"task":"<my pull requestuuid>","complete":false}}}

Example of some problem:

* if project as

{code}
#!text

https://bitbucket.org/<user>/project-foo
{code}

has been renamed to

{code}
#!text

https://bitbucket.org/<user>/project-bar
{code}

* And some friendly blogs, sites, twitter, etc., have a some discussion of the detail project with published url as

{code}
#!text

https://bitbucket.org/<user>/project-foo/commits/aabd5f3b9abde677659209c801ac9b4f5e845ee4
...
{code}

So we have a some problem after renaming in /project-foo/admin:

* will not exist all published earlier url ("Oops, you&#x27;ve found a dead link.")
* +issues

----
so needed redirect/alias settings */project-foo/* -> */project-bar/* e.g.:

* from:

{code}
#!text

https://bitbucket.org/<user>/project-foo/commits/aabd5f3b9abde677659209c801ac9b4f5e845ee4
{code}

* to  :

{code}
#!text

https://bitbucket.org/<user>/project-bar/commits/aabd5f3b9abde677659209c801ac9b4f5e845ee4
{code}

and other,

i.e. when user clicked old link he should see her in a new place without "Oops..." (optional, of course)

